            <div property="schema:text" class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item">
<h2>About Elgin, Oregon</h2>
<p>Elgin is nestled at the foot of the Blue Mountains on the northern edge of the Grande Ronde Valley. It is within 20 minutes north of driving time of La Grande, the site of Eastern Oregon University. Both La Grande and Eastern provide outstanding cultural and education opportunities for Elgin residents.</p>
<p>Approximately 2,000 citizens reside in the growing Elgin community. Many community members actively participate in school programs and provide continued support for school activities.</p>
<p>Elgin citizens, including school staff, work together to build a supportive community. Activities include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Youth Sports Programs</li>
<li>Public Library</li>
<li>Community Center</li>
<li>Swimming Pool</li>
<li>Booster Club</li>
<li>Nine Churches</li>
</ul>
<p>For more information about our community and the city of Elgin, visit <a href="http://www.visitelginoregon.com/" rel="nofollow">www.visitelginoregon.com</a> or click below:</p>
<p class="rtecenter"><a href="http://www.visitelginoregon.com/" rel="nofollow"><img alt=" Photo: Elgin City Panoramic" height="146" src="/sites/elgin.k12.or.us/files/Image/town/ph_elgin-panoramic.jpg" width="521"></a></p>
